==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[convenire]]; [[con-]] + [[venire]]'' to come.

===Verb===
{{en-verb|conven|ing}}

# {{cattag|intransitive}}: To come together; to meet; to unite.
# {{cattag|intransitive}}: To come together, as in one body or for a public purpose; to meet; to assemble.
# {{cattag|transitive}}: To cause to assemble; to call together; to convoke.
# {{cattag|transitive}}: To summon judicially to meet or appear.

====Synonyms====
*to [[meet]] (1, 2)
*to [[assemble]] (1, 2)
*to [[congregate]] (1, 2)
*to [[collect]] (1, 2)
*to [[unite]] (1, 2)

